      <hedline>
        <hl1>Far From Gandhi's Path</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Howard Slatkin letter, commenting on May 8 article, says resistance by Canadian gun owners to new registration requirement is not act of 'civil disobedience' (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>To describe the resistance of Canadian gun owners to new registration requirements as ''civil disobedience'' (''Across Canada's Mild West, Gun Rebels Glower,'' Edmonton Journal, May 8) does a disservice to the legacies of Mohandas K. Gandhi and the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>To describe the resistance of Canadian gun owners to new registration requirements as ''civil disobedience'' (''Across Canada's Mild West, Gun Rebels Glower,'' Edmonton Journal, May 8) does a disservice to the legacies of Mohandas K. Gandhi and the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.</p>
        <p>While gun owners who object to the laws make no explicit threats of violence, implicit in their resistance is the fact that they are armed and capable of violence. An adherent of the true principles of civil disobedience cannot be packing a firearm.</p>
        <p>HOWARD SLATKIN  New York, May 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
